id: pm-dvwm
title: "Replace template filler docstrings (about 4,100 occurrences) with informative docs and lint against the filler phrases"
description: Replace mass-generated filler docstrings with concise semantic documentation and add a ratcheted lint or census so coverage remains complete while token cost and misleading boilerplate decline.
type: Chore
status: open
priority: 3
tags[5]: "area:docs",code-quality,docstrings,maintainability,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-19T04:07:16.881Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-22T18:25:05.485Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 240
acceptance_criteria: "Census script or lint rule flags the known filler templates (Implements X for the public runtime surface of this module; Value that configures or reports X for this contract; Provides CLI runtime support for X; payload exchanged by command, SDK, and package integrations) and the count is ratcheted down, not up; Touched-file burn-down policy documented so gate-mandated docstrings added going forward must carry real information (what the value means, units, invariants) or use @inheritDoc/type-level docs; Static-gate docstring coverage stays at 100 percent throughout - the fix is content quality, never coverage relaxation"
parent: pm-n7rr
risk: low
confidence: 70
dependencies[2]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
