  pm-fb3i,related,"2026-07-19T04:07:16.881Z",null,null
body: "The 100 percent docstring gates (source/exported/member) incentivized mass template docstrings that satisfy coverage while carrying zero information: grep counts 622 'Implements X for the public runtime surface of this module', 2,945 'Value that configures or reports X for this contract' across 135 files, plus 543 'Provides CLI runtime support for X'/'payload exchanged by command, SDK, and package integrations' variants - about 4,100 filler lines. Cost: inflated file length (the 3400-LOC gate deliberately excludes comment lines, but agents reading files still pay the tokens), noise for agent context assembly, and docs that answer nothing (example: ExtensionCommandArgumentHelpDescriptor.name documented as 'Value that configures or reports name for this contract'). This is content-quality simplification under pm-n7rr; distinct from pm-fb3i (coverage floors) and pm-gvnj (DeepSource docs category)."
